      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t10-13.1",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "10-13.1",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t10-13.1-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-1"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-2"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-3"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-4"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.1-5"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "number describing a particular state of a quantum system",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "Electron states determine the binding energy stem:[E = E(n,l,m,j,s,f)] in an atom.\n\nUpper case letters stem:[N, L, M, J, S, F] are usually used for the whole system.\n\nThe spatial probability distribution of an electron is given by stem:[abs(ii(Psi))^2], where stem:[ii(Psi)] is its wave function. For an electron in an stem:[\"H\"] atom in a non-relativistic approximation, the wave function can be presented as:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nii(Psi)(r,vartheta,phi) = R_(nl)*Y_l^m (vartheta,phi)\n++++\n\nwhere\n\nstem:[r, vartheta, phi] are spherical coordinates (<<iso80000-2>>) with respect to the nucleus and to a given (quantization) axis, stem:[R_(nl)(r)] is the radial distribution function, and stem:[Y_l^m(vartheta,phi)] are spherical harmonics.\n\nIn the Bohr model of one-electron atoms, stem:[n], stem:[l], and stem:[m] define the possible orbits of an electron about the nucleus.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-10"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t10-13.2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "principal quantum number",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t10-13.2",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "10-13.2",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t10-13.2-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.2-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "atomic quantum number related to the number stem:[n-1] of radial nodes of one-electron wave functions",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "In the Bohr model, stem:[n = 1,2,...,oo] is related to the binding energy of an electron and the radius of spherical orbits (principal axis of the elliptic orbits).\n\nFor an electron in an stem:[\"H\"] atom, the semi-classical radius of its orbit is stem:[r_n = a_0n^2] and its binding energy is stem:[E_n = E_\"H\"//n^2].\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-10"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t10-13.3-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "orbital angular momentum quantum number",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t10-13.3-0",
